<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="277" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 437.00/49.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Cuban Congress adjourned March 26 without acting on the Guantanamo
                            matter. New Congress convenes April 6.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Note.</hi>—The proposed treaty expired by
                                limitation June 27, 1913, since by its article 5 a stipulation was
                                made for its ratification within six months from its date: December
                                27, 1912. See <ref target="frus1912#pg_297">For. Rel. 1912, p.
                                    297</ref>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>